  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Set up in the standing tall with one load at side. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the standing tall with one load at side.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, band, cable, bar, or body position as appropriate.","Hold for about 20 seconds or the prescribed effort window while breathing under control.","End the set as soon as alignment, breathing, pain-free range, or target-tissue tension changes."],"coach_cues":["Stand tall like the weight is trying to bend you","Shoulders level","Crush the handle and breathe"],"athlete_cues":["Own the angle.","Pressure without panic.","Breathe while you hold."],"breathing_cues":["No breath-holding contest.","Small exhale through the brace.","Reset breath between hard efforts."],"common_faults":["Leaning away from the load","Grip fails before posture is trained","Holding breath to make the hold longer"],"quality_gate":"Rep counts only when the athlete holds the chosen angle with steady pressure, controlled breathing, and no visible compensation.","stop_signs":["Pain, pinch, numbness, tingling, dizziness, or headache","Breath holding that cannot be corrected","Alignment changes or shaking becomes uncontrolled","Unsafe equipment, anchor, wall, rack, or landing setup"]}'::jsonb,
