  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Set up in the kneeling Nordic lean hold at owned angle. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the kneeling Nordic lean hold at owned angle.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, band, cable, bar, or body position as appropriate.","Hold for about 6 seconds or the prescribed effort window while breathing under control.","End the set as soon as alignment, breathing, pain-free range, or target-tissue tension changes."],"coach_cues":["Hold the body angle you own","Hips stay tall","Exit before the fall surprises you"],"athlete_cues":["Own the angle.","Pressure without panic.","Breathe while you hold."],"breathing_cues":["No breath-holding contest.","Small exhale through the brace.","Reset breath between hard efforts."],"common_faults":["Hinging at hips to escape tension","Chasing long holds too early","Cramping or sharp pain ignored"],"quality_gate":"Rep counts only when the athlete holds the chosen angle with steady pressure, controlled breathing, and no visible compensation.","stop_signs":["Pain, pinch, numbness, tingling, dizziness, or headache","Breath holding that cannot be corrected","Alignment changes or shaking becomes uncontrolled","Unsafe equipment, anchor, wall, rack, or landing setup"]}'::jsonb,
